                    <p>Students can access these soft copies anywhere through mobile or tablets and can study from it. Students should be well versed with the syllabus right at the beginning of the academic session. This will help them in knowing the topics that they will study in each subject during the entire year. Also, they can prepare an effective study plan for themselves. Referring to the NCERT Syllabus, students can easily track what all topics they have covered till now and what needs to be completed. This helps them in finishing the syllabus on time so that students get time for revision.</p>

                    <h3>NCERT Question Papers</h3>
                    <p>The question papers are prepared by the CBSE and other boards in accordance with the NCERT exam guidelines. Here, we have provided online question papers for class 6 to 12 and objective type questions for all classes. By solving them students will get an idea about the question paper pattern, types of questions asked, marks distribution and important topics. These question papers will be more helpful for the class 10 and 12 board exam students. So, make the most of it by not missing any chance of scoring high marks in the board exams.</p>

                    <h3>NCERT Notes Online</h3>
                    <p>NCERT notes are helpful especially during revision. Students must build a habit of making notes while studying. Students get everything written in a short and compiled form. It helps them in remembering important points and formulas. Just merely going through the notes, students recall all the concepts without going through the textbooks. So, here we have provided chapter wise NCERT Notes online for all subjects for class 6 to 12 students. Go through them and get key points of each chapter.</p>
